rComments: Literally my favourite prof at UTSC. He's so kind and caring and actually a really good lecturer! He may seem dry at first but he's still really good at explaining concepts. Also, HE ACTUALLY RESPONDS TO EMAILS (unlike other profs). Nothing bad to say about this guy at all!

Here is everything you need to know about him for psych and the law: 1) Boring lecturer 2) the first 30 questions of his exam are always from the lectures 3) the last 70 questions from his exam are all from the textbook 4) Lecture material on the exam is free marks if you listen to the lecture. 5) He tests mostly on details (names, concept names)

As long as you watch the weboption, go through the lecture notes, you will be fine. Most of the lecture notes are pretty much summaries of the assigned chapters, so it saved me tons of time to figure out what is important and what can be left out when reviewing.
Good caring professor, but the lectures were boring. Only two tests, both worth 50%. If you want a course that has all multiple choice exams this may be the class for you.

His monotone makes you difficult to stay focus in class, but his personal stories are interesting and inspiring to hear. He spent most of the lecture time on things that are not related to the text or the tests. Tests are not fair in my opinion. He rarely test you on theories but some random year and percentages indicated from the text.
Easy class. But attend lectures or get notes because some stuff he says isn't in the textbook.

Nussbaum is a really sweet guy! He's a bit boring in lecture, but really wants you to learn and the exams do not test small details. Make sure to read the textbook and take good notes. If you study those and read the lecture slides, you'll do well. He'll help you if you need it!

In short and keeping it as professional as possible: No matter what class you take with him, don't have high expectations. Psych and law is a great topic but he ruins it completely. He goes on irrelevant rants with offensive topics and comments. It takes him 2 hrs to get through 1040 slides. He takes slides from publishers so all book stuff.

He's a really great guy and loves his work and the subject. You only really get through like 4 slides in the two hours because he goes on rants. He does test you on the lectures though, so it is good! Basically memorize the textbook but he is very approachable and helpful!

his lectures are very boring. he can talk about 1 topic for an hour and ends up always rushing through slides in the end. The exams are based on the textbook, so going to his class won't be helpful in understanding the materials nor helpful for the exam. I dont think I have learned anything important or something to take away with me in the future.

Amazing professor. He is the most helpful, attentive professor on this campus- he actually cares if your learning and tries to help you succeed if you are willing. He reads from the slides but the guy has 900 other things going on! really interesting research! over, best prof.
awesome guy. fountain of knowledge and experience learn from him! really wants to help his students if you give him time to.

Rants a lot. Course is very repetitive. All important slides are taken from textbook. Attendance not mandatory. He basically just talks on and on about the same thing. Spends hours on one slide. Tries to cover too much in not enough time. Gets sidetracked by pointless stories. Nice guy, but lecture is very boring and pointless.

He explains things very clearly. Overall hes a good professor. Although, his lecture style is very boring and everything he says is right from the textbook. He talks really slow and never gets to the point becuase hes always rambling on.
Great professor. Very helpful and down to earth. Easy to talk to. Enjoyed being in his class.

He didn't keep on track. Very very disorganized for a university professor. He could not even finish his power point slides ever, he was always side tracked by a story. He relied 100% on the text book, which is boring. I can read the text myself, I don't need someone else to read it so me. I wasn't happy with this course.

Guys, cool off. Dr Nussbaum is an AMAZING professor that teaches qualitatively not quantitatively. We should have more profs like him at UTSC! He is BRILLIANT and shares his knowledge generously. Forensic Psych is hard stuff. I don't want an easy A. I want to learn something! Best prof!
His course sucks period. You pay $500 to know there are wackos in the world (booorrring). Take crime and devianc instead--far more interesting than this course!

A really down to earth professor. His exams are completely multiple choice. He doesn't try to trick you on the test as long as you read the text and know it by heart. he did make the final a bit harder just to bell curve the marks, but the class avg was high so its fair game.
Crystal clear teaching. Very helpful and friendly. If you read the textbook you're basically golden. Thanks for the A!

he has lots of experience in forensic psychology and is an intelligent prof but he is frequently late to class, doesn't post lecture notes in advance and is overall, disorganized. it makes me feel like he is too busy to care about lecturing us.
Easy going and relaxed professor. The material is useful and you can relate it to real life/events. His exams are straightforward and fair if you read the textbook and understand the terms.
very easy going, fair and funny. would take another course with him

This was an enjoyable class. He is a funny prof, and does his best to keep students interested. I liked hearing of his experiences with the legal system. The first 2 midterms were fair but the final was tricky, but I guess that was to bring the high class average down. Would take another class with him again.
He is very fair and funny.

awesome guy.  soooo funny.  his classes are not mandatory to attend, but are worth going because you will be laughing the entire time.  i found this course to be fairly easy.  You do need to read the text book.  The exams are VERY straight forward and obvious if you have done the readings.  -no tricks

Naussbaum is too funny. This guy was always late to class, never seemed to know what was going on and frequently went off topic. But I really liked this class. When he does focus on what the topic of the lecture is he's good & has a lot of practical experience in forensic psyc which he uses as examples. Overall a good course, and exams were easy.
Definetly one of the best Psych Profs!
